item.dc:creator: @unlimitedorb unlimitedorb
item.description:
@unlimitedorb wrote:

Mopman:

So is my name IRL a mnemonic for my face?

How is bundy’s use of the term not a mnemonic?

Consider The Java Virtual Machine Specification’s use of the term. The character sequences associated with opcodes are referred to as mnemonics. Humans don’t innately recognize numbers because most of them have no associated semantics. It’s not a stretch to say that associating meaningful names to obfuscated program data and constructs fits the form of the definition for a mnemonic.

In fact, I would make the argument that your face is a mnemonic for your name

EDIT:

Disclaimer - This post in no way reflects my blind devotion to the fantastically sexy Mr. PSB. As all great minds are apt to do, he got bored and decided to stir things up. It’s like a breath of fresh air. I tried to do the same, but it seemed as though people weren’t ready for it. It’s no secret that the threads on MITB have been stagnant and devoid of creativity lately.

I commend your effort to defend the Wizard of Oz that is PSB, Mopman. I was too cowardly to do so myself. I have sinned.
